rComments: Awesome professor, she was a great lecturer and super organized. Her powerpoints were very well built and she always allowed for discussion in class. Skimming the readings and then paying closer attention to the ones needed for assignments was enough. Her quizzes and exams were easy if you payed attention. Overall it was a very enjoyable class.

I was hesitant taking this course since their were so many bad reviews, however this was my favourite course in during my semester! She is engaging and very clear what she wants from you in the papers. We had to write 2 papers, and there were 3 quizzes (pretty easy), final there was an online final and if you attended class you should be just fine.

Awful! Her class is badly organised has too many TAs. Most of the time you do not know who graded your paper. there is no clear grading scheme. Grading by her so by her TAs is subjective. Gives celebrities as examples for feminists who are far from being a feminist. she gives a celebrity example after each class. alot of pointless howrk and papers.

Elle est superbe! Très passionnée par le sujet! Ses powerpoints sont bien rempli, mais elle ajoute tellement de personnalité à la matière, ça vaut la peine d'aller au cours! On avait 3 quiz de "présence," avec des dates préétablit et qui valaient 10% chaque. Super facile! Un examen en classe (facile aussi!) et un examen maison. Très bonne prof!
Correction strict même si tu mets 4h dans un projet......... Pour matiere tellement simple ?

Worst prof ever! She tells you that sheS giving presence points but its actually pop quiz..I was their every classes and I only got 7 points out of 12! On one of my paper I got 20on30 but behind my 20 I could see a 25 but it got erased..I had hooks every wear in my paper but I got 66%, no comments NOTHING!The only thing she does is read her notes!
